'''Dragon Warrior IV''' (known as '''Dragon Quest IV''' in Japan) is a role-playing video game developed by Chunsoft and published by Enix for the Nintendo Entertainment System. It was released in Japan on February 11, 1990 and in North America in October 1992. It is the fourth installment in the Dragon Quest series.

==Overview==

Dragon Warrior IV is notable for its chapter-based storytelling structure, where players control different protagonists across five chapters before the stories converge. The game features an AI-controlled party system in the final chapter, where party members make their own decisions in battle based on "tactics" settings.

